Package com.spotify.sdk.android.playback

Contains classes used for playing music.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ConnectionStateCallback
    Callback used to deliver information about connection state events.
    NativePlayer
    Any native player that connects to Spotify playback services must implement this interface.
    NativePlayer.AudioDeliveredCallback
    Interface used to register callback for audio data received from native player.
    NativePlayer.AudioFlushCallback
    Interface used to register callback for audio flush command received from native player.
    Player.InitializationObserver
    Observer interface used to know when the player is fully initialized.
    PlayerNotificationCallback
    Callback used to send player events to an observer
    PlayerStateCallback  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AudioRingBuffer
    A ring buffer to hold audio data before they can be written to the audio output.
    Config
    This class is used to pass configuration parameters to the native SDK layer.
    Config.DeviceType
    The SDK represents device types as raw integers, but rather than dealing with an enum an abstract class is used, as we are missing some intermediate values and require a bit more granularity here than an enum can offer.
    Connectivity
    Class used for sending connectivity messages to the SDK.
    NativeSdkPlayer
    Bridge to the SDK's native player.
    PlayConfig
    This object can be passed to Player.play(PlayConfig) method if more control over playback is required.
    Player
    This class is responsible for playback of Spotify content.
    PlayerState
    Class which holds information about the current player state
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    PlayerNotificationCallback.ErrorType
    Various types of playback errors that can be sent from the native player
    PlayerNotificationCallback.EventType
    Various event types which the player can send
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NativeSpotifyException
    Exception used for any error which has occurred in the native side of the SDK
